[Dr. Clement makes a good case for considering Seoul hantavirus
infection in establishing diagnoses for these cases. And there is no
law against this being an outbreak of multiple etiologies. But
ruling out possible etiologies and establishing others requires
comprehensive laboratory support (one peek [in the lab] is worth a
thousand guesses). Jamaica may not have the capability of testing
for SEOV, but I am sure the CDC or other labs would be willing to
test for it. In any event, the response is the same -- rapidly
reduce the rat population. - Mod.TY]
